      "source": "<a href=\"http://twitter.com/download/iphone\" rel=\"nofollow\">Twitter for iPhone</a>",
      "text": "Layered security against unlawful maritime migration.\n \nWorking with our partners @CBP and @USMC, the crew of #USCG Cutter Thetis interdicted an overloaded, makeshift vessel Friday in the Mona Passage near Puerto Rico. We safely embarked and transferred the 60 people aboard to the Dominican Republic Navy for repatriation.\n\nOur message is clear: illegal migrant voyages are dangerous, and you will be repatriated.\n\nAlways ready, the men and women of the Coast Guard remain on watch across our maritime borders and approaches, where defense of America begins.\n\nRead more: https://t.co/X5bC0UWB0W\n\n#USCG #WeOwnTheSea #SemperParatus #MaritimeDominance\n@DHSgov",
      "text_resolved": "Layered security against unlawful maritime migration.\n \nWorking with our partners @CBP and @USMC, the crew of #USCG Cutter Thetis interdicted an overloaded, makeshift vessel Friday in the Mona Passage near Puerto Rico. We safely embarked and transferred the 60 people aboard to the Dominican Republic Navy for repatriation.\n\nOur message is clear: illegal migrant voyages are dangerous, and you will be repatriated.\n\nAlways ready, the men and women of the Coast Guard remain on watch across our maritime borders and approaches, where defense of America begins.\n\nRead more: https://www.news.uscg.mil/Press-Releases/Article/4447618/coast-guard-repatriates-60-aliens-to-dominican-republic-following-unlawful-migr/\n\n#USCG #WeOwnTheSea #SemperParatus #MaritimeDominance\n@DHSgov",
